<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="539" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,294,320]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Comparison.</emphasis>
<materialsCitation location="Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Pernambuco">
Material compared to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[614,914,295,321]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis box="[614,914,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pattersoncypris salitrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nº DGEO-CTG-UFPE-1971 and Nº DGEO- CTG-UFPE-1166), described and deposited by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[680,886,331,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[749,798,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al</emphasis>
. (2014)
</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:31296775CE7AFFF386B7F9BD9DD2FC41:BC5F80B8CE7DFFF385E0FE899FE8FE49" name="Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" stateProvince="Pernambuco">Ivan de Medeiros Tinoco Microfossils Collection</location>
</emphasis>
of the Paleontology Laboratory of the Federal University of 
<collectingRegion box="[910,1054,367,393]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,592,402,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Occurrence and associated fauna</emphasis>
. It was recorded in the Santo Antonio section, at the following depths (from base to top): 0.3; 1.8; 2.1; 2.25; 2.65; 3.4; 3.65; 3.85; 4.05 and 
<quantity box="[867,949,438,465]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" unit="m" value="4.25">4.25 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" baseAuthorityYear="1971" box="[961,1104,439,465]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salitrensis">
<emphasis box="[961,1104,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">P. salitrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is associated with all species of ostracods, except 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poag" authorityYear="1962" box="[385,521,475,500]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cuneocytheridae" genus="Dicrorygma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[385,521,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Dicrorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Christensen" authorityYear="1965" box="[539,677,475,501]" class="Ostracoda" genus="Orthorygma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[539,677,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Orthorygma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
?) 
<emphasis box="[707,816,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">dimorpha</emphasis>
Weiss and 
<taxonomicName authority="Krommelbein &amp; Weber." class="Ostracoda" family="Podocopida (awaiting allocation)" genus="Theriosynoecum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinodosum">
<emphasis box="[947,1132,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Theriosynoecum</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[1177,1353,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">quadrinodosum</emphasis>
Krömmelbein &amp; Weber.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,546,572]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Observations</emphasis>
. The specimens recovered were compared to the illustrations of 
<taxonomicName authority="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" authorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cretapa">
<emphasis box="[1085,1355,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Pattersoncypris cretapa</emphasis>
Krömmelbein &amp; Weber
</taxonomicName>
, published in 
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Whatley, R. &amp; Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C." box="[500,760,583,609]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="790 - 799" refId="ref13890" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Whatley, R., Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. (2008) On the validity of two Lower Cretaceous non-marine ostracode genera: biostratigraphic and paleogeographic implications. Journal of Paleontology, 82, 790 - 799. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 07 - 008.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[622,677,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
. Some similarities were seen, but a comparison between both specimens is necessary for a future synonymy of these species. The Santo Antônio site is one of the few sections that marks the boundary between the Aptian and lower Albian in the Romualdo Formation. It is worth mentioning that this species was not recorded in the lower Albian at this locality (
<bibRefCitation author="Araripe, R. &amp; Pedrosa Lemos, F. A. &amp; do Prado, L. A. C. &amp; Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Oliveira, D. H. D. &amp; Pereira, P. A. &amp; Nascimento, L. R. S. L. &amp; Asakura, Y. &amp; Ng, C. &amp; Viviers, M. C. &amp; Barreto, A. F." box="[880,1099,691,717]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="103814" refId="ref12694" refString="Araripe, R., Pedrosa Lemos, F. A., do Prado, L. A. C., Tome, M. E. T. R., Oliveira, D. H. D., Pereira, P. A., Nascimento, L. R. S. L., Asakura, Y., Ng, C., Viviers, M. C. &amp; Barreto, A. F. (2022) Upper Aptian - lower Albian of the southern-central Araripe Basin, Brazil: Microbiostratigraphic and paleoecological inferences. Journal of South American Earth Sciences, 116, 103814. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jsames. 2022.103814" type="journal article" year="2022">
Araripe 
<emphasis box="[975,1031,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
2022
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,150,897]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,509,726,752]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Stratigraphic distribution</emphasis>
. In 
<collectingCountry box="[555,626,727,753]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, distributed in the Araripe Basin, Santana Group (above the layers with fish occurrence), Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R." box="[435,766,763,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref15025" refString="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R. (1971) Ostracoden des &quot; Nordost-Brasilianischen Wealden &quot;. Geologisches Jahrbuch, 115, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1971">Krommelbein &amp; Weber 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bate, R. H." box="[778,895,763,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="283 - 292" refId="ref13105" refString="Bate, R. H. (1999) Non-marine ostracod assemblages of the Pre-Salt rift basins of West Africa and their role in sequence stratigraphy. In: Cameron, N. R., Bate, R. H. &amp; Clure, V. S. (Eds.), The Oil and Gas Habitats of the South Atlantic. Geological Society of London Special Publication, 153, pp. 283 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1144 / GSL. SP. 1999.153.01.17" type="journal article" year="1999">Bate 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P." box="[906,1168,763,789]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="772 - 798" refId="ref16184" refString="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P. (2012 a) Early Cretaceous ostracod biostratigraphy of eastern Brazil and western Africa: An overview. Gondwana Research, 22, 772 - 798. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. gr. 2012.06.002" type="journal article" year="2012">Poropat &amp; Colin 2012a</bibRefCitation>
) and Romualdo Formation, lower Albian (
<bibRefCitation author="Tome, M. E. T. R. &amp; Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L." box="[369,564,799,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="153 - 176" refId="ref17084" refString="Tome, M. E. T. R., Lima Filho, M. F. &amp; Neumann, V. H. M. L. (2014) Taxonomic studies of non-marine ostracods in the Lower Cretaceous (Aptian-lower Albian) of post-rift sequence from Jatoba and Araripe basins (Northeast Brazil): Stratigraphic implications. Cretaceous Research, 48, 153 - 176. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2013.12.007" type="journal article" year="2014">
Tomé 
<emphasis box="[441,498,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Araripe, R. &amp; Oliveira, D. &amp; Tome, M. E. &amp; Mello, R. M. &amp; Barreto, A. M. F." box="[574,789,799,825]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="104766" refId="ref12613" refString="Araripe, R., Oliveira, D., Tome, M. E., Mello, R. M. &amp; Barreto, A. M. F. (2021) Foraminifera and Ostracoda from the lower Cretaceous (Aptian - lower Albian) Romualdo formation, Araripe Basin, northeast Brazil: Paleoenvironmental inferences. Cretaceous Research, 122, 104766. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. cretres. 2021.104766" type="journal article" year="2021">
Araripe 
<emphasis box="[666,723,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
); Grajaú Basin, Codó Formation, upper Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Ramos, M. I. F. &amp; Rossetti, D. D. F. &amp; Paz, J. S." pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="339 - 348" refId="ref16386" refString="Ramos, M. I. F., Rossetti, D. D. F. &amp; Paz, J. S. (2006) Caracterizacao e significado paleoambiental da fauna de ostracodes da Formacao Codo (Neoaptiano), leste da Bacia de Grajau, MA, Brasil. Revista Brasileira de Paleontologia, 9, 339 - 348. https: // doi. org / 10.4072 / rbp. 2006.3.09" type="journal article" year="2006">
Ramos 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
); Potiguar Basin, Alagamar Formation, Aptian (
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Whatley, R. &amp; Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C." box="[790,1043,835,861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="539" pagination="790 - 799" refId="ref13890" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Whatley, R., Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. (2008) On the validity of two Lower Cretaceous non-marine ostracode genera: biostratigraphic and paleogeographic implications. Journal of Paleontology, 82, 790 - 799. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 07 - 008.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[917,975,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="539">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
). In the present study, found in the Araripe Basin, Romualdo Formation, upper Aptian.
</paragraph>
